---
alwaysApply: true
---

When working with backend API calls (implementing, debugging, or adding endpoints),
use the OpenAPI spec as the source of truth: curl -s http://localhost:8000/openapi.json.
Refer to it for paths, methods, request/response schemas, and types.
When you need the spec, fetch it via the shell (e.g. curl -s http://localhost:8000/openapi.json);
the web fetch tool cannot reach localhost.
